      {
         "text": "#### The Arrival of Europeans\n\nThe European colonization of South America (known as *Abya Yala* by Indigenous peoples) brought profound changes, including a demographic collapse that reduced Indigenous populations by millions (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).\n\nAdditionally, the Treaty of Tordesillas (**Figura 2**) (<htcite2>) wimposed territorial divisions without Indigenous consent.",
