         "text": "<center><span class=\"desc\"><img id=\"bndPortugal6r\" src=\"images/BibliotecaNacionalDigital/BNDTordesillas_6r.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('bndPortugal6r', '0%')\" />Figure 2: Page from the <i>Tratado de Tordesillas</i> mentioning Rui Leme (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('086440f2-0df7-4589-ac73-0353cf1b5312'); return false;\">Biblioteca Nacional de Portugal - BNP, BN MS. 5, n.º 25, F. 6r</a>). <span id=\"bndPortugal\"></span>).</span></center></p><p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: On Land Division</b><br /><br />Imagine a scenario where a group of people gathers for a meeting and decides to divide the world among themselves, claiming ownership of everything that has been built over millennia. Would you feel comfortable with the idea of being left with nothing?</div></div></center>",
         "source": null,
         "date_time": null,
